@node "Introduction" "Introduction to IdleWOS"
@next "Introduction"
@prev "Introduction"

@{JCENTER}@{b}@{u}Introduction@{ub}@{uu}

@{b}IdleWOS@{ub} is an @{u}instrument@{uu} to see how busy the ppc (& a68k:) processor is. Nothing more, nothing less.
This program is great if you want to find out if your (or any) ppc (or a68k) program takes too much cpu-time.
And if so, you want to reduce it. You can also use this program to see if your program is @{u}really@{uu} on the job.

This version of @{b}IdleWOS@{ub} is for WarpOS @{u}and@{uu} for A68k !!!
It supports A68K again, but don't expect too much. @{u}@{b}This is experimental and might be buggy !!!@{ub}@{uu}

The a68k support I've added @{i}needs@{ui} the sysinfo.library/sysmon.library and StartSM. Without it, it can't and won't work.

@endnode

@node "Requirements" "Requirements for IdleWOS"
@next "Requirements"
@prev "Requirements"

@{JCENTER}@{b}@{u}Requirements@{ub}@{uu}

@{b}IdleWOS@{ub} requires an Amiga with at least @{b}V44 (OS 3.5)@{ub},
a @{b}PPC@{ub} processor, @{b}WarpOS@{ub} installed, sysinfo.library/sysmon.library and not too much memory.
It also @{b}@{u}needs@{uu}@{ub} StartSM from the sysmon package.
If you wanna use ScreenNotify, install screennotify.library 1.x in libs:


@endnode

@node "History" "Idle History"
@next "History"
@prev "History"

@{JCENTER}@{b}@{u}History@{ub}@{uu}
@{JLEFT}
 V1.01-1.023     -  For internal use only.
 V1.024 & 1.027  -  First public release.
 V1.100  28/01/2001 - New GUI (GTLayout).
 V1.101  01/02/2001 - Made the response a bit better.
 V1.102  15/02/2001 - Fixed some enforcer hits. Code cleanup. Added tooltype TEN.
 V1.103  19/02/2001 - Small fix.
 V1.104  20/02/2001 - Kicked 1 patchwork hit out. Added 'text in gauge'.
 V1.105  27/02/2001 - Added CPU check routine. Added tooltype for 'text in gauge'.
 V1.32   09/08/2001 - Added WOS Support :) Dropped A68K support :( Added some new tooltypes.
 V1.33   12/08/2001 - Bugfix in SystemLoad check. Small changes.
 V1.52   25/12/2001 - New version which uses the reaction classes. LOAD is now a switch. Added DELAY tooltype.
 V1.52b  11/01/2002 - Made IdleWOS check for window.class V45+ as the V44 (OS3.5) version crashes!
 V1.53   17/01/2002 - Enabled the XPOS & YPOS ToolTypes again and fixed the ReadArgs() somewhat.
 V1.54   11/02/2002 - Added window width & height arguments/tooltypes.
 V1.60   17/02/2002 - Added changable colors. Added experimental ARexx Port (for my eyes only :).
 V1.61   25/05/2002 - Added a possible check for G3's & G4's (untested). Squashed the window refresh bug. As it turned out,
                      I had to set LAYOUT_DeferLayout to FALSE. Really strange, as you normally set LAYOUT_DeferLayout to TRUE (and leave it that way). 
 V1.62   30/05/2002 - Added TEXTPEN tooltype for changing the Layout TextPen.
 V1.63   12/06/2002 - Added a working check for G3, G4 & G5 processors.
 V1.64   20/11/2002 - Fixed the DELAY argument.
 V1.64b  24/11/2002 - IdleWOS wouldn't work on some machines. Fixed :)
 V1.65   22/12/2002 - Made IdleWOS now calculate an average value. Thx to Deniil for telling me.
 V1.66   15/05/2003 - Added A68k support under WOS, again :))
 V1.66   25/08/2005 - Recompiled with VBCC 0.8i and set -O3.
 V1.67b  07/05/2006 - Maintenance update.
 V1.68   18/05/2006 - Added vertical gauge bar. Fixed some bugs in window handling.
 V1.69   18/12/2006 - Added support for ScreenNotify.
 V1.69b  18/01/2007 - Kicked a bug that made it impossible to un-iconify.

@endnode

