@node "ToolTypes" "ToolTypes"
@next "ToolTypes"
@prev "ToolTypes"

@{JCENTER}@{b}@{u}ToolTypes@{ub}@{uu}
@{JLEFT}
 IdleWOS has a couple of tooltypes:

 XPOS & YPOS: Guess what they do !?
 LOAD: Shows the CPU & System Load at the same time.
 HORIZ: The fuelgauge gadgets will be next to each other. Default = Vertical.
 DELAY: Sets the delaytime in millisecs. Default = 250000.
 WIDTH & HEIGHT: Ehhhh ????
 PERCENTPEN: Changes the FuelGauge PercentPen color.
 FILLPEN: Changes the FuelGauge FillPen color.
 EMPTYPEN: Changes the FuelGauge EmptyPen color.
 TEXTPEN: Changes the Layout TextPen color.
 A68K: Enable the A68K FuelGauge.
 DOWN: Put the A68K FuelGauge at the bottom.
 VERT: Make a vertical gauge.

@endnode

