@node "Bugs" "Bugs, Ehhhhhhhh :("
@next "Bugs"
@prev "Bugs"

@{JCENTER}@{b}@{u}Bugs@{ub}@{uu}
@{JLEFT}
 · IdleWOS doesn't work correctly on V39/40 due to problems with the ClassAct/Reaction classes. Solution ? Upgrade !
 · Un-iconifying makes the window 8 pixels larger each time you do this. This is a bug in window.class V45, as V44 doesn't suffer from it.
   BTW: all Reaction programs have the same problem, afaik !!!
 · When using tooltypes/readargs WIDTH & HEIGHT you can't set below a certain value. However, you can do this afterwards, with the sizegadget.
   This is also a bug in the V45 window.class.
 · One out of two or three times the program is started from Workbench/Dopus, it doesn't make a GUI anymore (no crashes though).
   This only occurs if StartSM was been run, so be warned. Without it or running from the CLI, there's no problem.


@endnode

@node "Misc" "Miscellaneous"
@next "Misc"
@prev "Misc"

@{JCENTER}@{b}@{u}Misc@{ub}@{uu}
@{JLEFT}
 SystemLoad can and will be (sometimes) > 100%. This is normal. That's how WarpOS works.
 What it @{u}really@{uu} means <taken from WarpOS.guide>
  "@{b}The total system load in percent. This value states how many CPU's would be at least necessary
   to execute all running tasks at full speed. A sytem load of 500 percent means that at least 5 CPU's would be necessary.@{ub}"


 

@endnode

